CHAT SESSION CREATION FIX
=========================
Date: 2025-01-19
Issue: Documents uploaded before sending the first message were not being associated with the chat session

PROBLEM:
- Chat thread ID was only created when the user sent their first message
- Documents uploaded before the first message had no session ID
- This caused the RAG system to not find the documents

SOLUTION:
1. Modified startNewChat() function to create a backend session immediately when user clicks "New Chat"
2. Updated the function to:
   - Call createChatSession API to create a session in the database
   - Get the thread_id from the backend response
   - Set the thread_id in the store immediately
   
3. Updated EnhancedInputBox component to:
   - Accept threadId as a prop
   - Use the threadId from props for document uploads
   
4. Updated AnimatedChatContainer to:
   - Get threadId from the store
   - Pass it to EnhancedInputBox

FILES MODIFIED:
- /root/deer-flow/web/src/core/store/store.ts
  - Modified startNewChat() to be async and create session immediately
  - Uses backend-generated thread_id instead of client-side nanoid()
  
- /root/deer-flow/web/src/components/deer-flow/app-sidebar.tsx
  - Updated handleChatClick to be async to await startNewChat()
  
- /root/deer-flow/web/src/app/chat/components/enhanced-input-box.tsx
  - Added threadId prop to interface
  - Uses threadId prop for document uploads
  
- /root/deer-flow/web/src/app/chat/components/animated-chat-container.tsx
  - Gets threadId from store
  - Passes threadId to EnhancedInputBox

RESULT:
- When user clicks "New Chat", a session is created immediately with a thread_id
- Documents uploaded are now associated with the correct session from the start
- RAG system can find documents even before the first message is sent